gomodel:SYNGO_1160  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The authors show by combination of immunoblotting with functional assay (glutamate release assay) that Botulinum neurotoxin C1 is able to cleave specifically membrane-bound syntaxin-1 and this leads to inhibition of neurotransmitter release.\n\n4/9/2017 Pim\n- Glutamate release from synaptosomal preparations measured with a photospectrometric assay.. Experimental description: Materials and Methods:\nPreparation and incubation of subcellular fractions Synaptosomeswerepreparedasdescribedpreviouslybymeansofdiferential and Ficoll-gradient centrifugation (Fischer von Mollard etal., 1991; McMahonetal.,1992)\n\nIn addition, the fig. 1 and fig.2 legends." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1542-3498" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0808-7003" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3898-5197" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-30" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1160" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

